sights.name: Place de la Bourse
sights.quote: Iconic city square with 18th-century architecture, a fountain & a vast reflecting pool.
sights.address: Place de la Bourse, 33000 Bordeaux, France

sights.name: The Big Bell of Bordeaux
sights.quote: 7.75-ton 18th-century bell above a former dungeon for juveniles, rung on special occasions.

sights.name: Bordeaux Cathedral
sights.quote: Towering Romanesque cathedral dating to the 11th century, hosting regular services & organ recitals.

sights.name: Grand Théâtre de Bordeaux
sights.quote: This grand theatre with a façade dating from 1780 hosts operas, dance & music performances.
sights.address: Place de la Comédie, 33000 Bordeaux, France

sights.name: Cité du Vin
sights.quote: High-tech wine museum with interactive displays & tastings in a curved aluminum & glass building.

sights.name: Monument aux Girondins
sights.quote: Monument with a fountain & towering column erected to honor Girondin revolutionaries.

sights.name: Cailhau Gate Bordeaux
sights.quote: Built in 1495, this monument with a castle-like exterior was once the main gate to the city.

sights.name: jardin public
sights.quote: Public green space with an arboretum & large lake, plus a natural history museum & a puppet theater.
sights.address: Jardin Public, Cours de Verdun, 33000 Bordeaux, France

sights.name: Le miroir d'eau
sights.quote: Built in 2006 by the Place de la Bourse, this reflecting pool is one of the world's largest.
sights.address: Place de la Bourse, 33000 Bordeaux, France

sights.name: Musée d'Aquitaine
sights.quote: History museum featuring a wealth of artifacts & sculpture from Bordeaux's prehistory until today.

sights.name: Pey Berland Tower
sights.quote: The 15th-century Gothic bell tower of the cathedral, offering far-reaching views of the city.

sights.name: Musée du Vin et du Négoce de Bordeaux
sights.orig_name: Musée du Vin et du Négoce de Bordeaux
sights.quote: Old equipment & new technology from 2000 years of wine production in the region, plus tastings.

sights.name: Jacques Chaban-Delmas Bridge
sights.quote: This 2013 concrete-&-steel bridge features a deck that stays parallel as it lifts for passing ships.
sights.address: Pont Jacques Chaban Delmas, 33300 Bordeaux, France

sights.name: palais Gallien
sights.quote: Remains of a Roman amphitheater dating to the 3rd century CE, with a multimedia visitor center.
sights.address: 126 Rue du Dr Albert Barraud, 33000 Bordeaux, France

sights.name: Museum of Fine Arts of Bordeaux
sights.orig_name: Museum of Fine Arts of Bordeaux
sights.quote: Elegant art museum with large collections of classical art from the Renaissance to the 19th century.

sights.name: Parliament Square
sights.quote: Historic square named after the Bordeaux Parliament, featuring an ornate fountain & cafes.

sights.name: Basilica of Saint Michael, Bordeaux
sights.quote: Basilica built in the flamboyant Gothic style with a separate tower, crypt & 19th-century organ.

sights.name: Botanical Garden
sights.quote: Botanical gardens with a water garden, an arboretum & glasshouses conserving local plant species.

sights.name: CAPC Museum of Contemporary Art of Bordeaux
sights.orig_name: CAPC Museum of Contemporary Art of Bordeaux
sights.quote: 19th-century warehouse housing contemporary art museum with temporary shows & notable collection.

sights.name: Pont de pierre
sights.quote: Commissioned by Napoleon, this elegant bridge has 17 spans enabling it to cross the River Garonne.
